name: Baron, Barry C.
title: Physician, MD
notes: Dr. Barry C. Baron is an ENT-otolaryngologist in San Francisco, CA, who received his medical degree from UCSF School of Medicine in 1975 and completed residency at UCSF Affiliated Hospitals. He is affiliated with Brown and Toland Physicians and Sutter Health, practicing at 2100 Webster Street, San Francisco.

name: Busterud, James P.
title: Founder, CFP
notes: James Busterud is a Certified Financial Planner who founded Jack Point Advisors in 2017, an independent RIA based in Novato, CA. He has over 23 years of investment experience with prior roles as Senior Vice President and Senior Portfolio Manager at Merrill Lynch, Morgan Stanley, and UBS. He attended Pomona College (economics and music) and Eastman School of Music, and performed professionally as a singer for 17 years before returning to finance.

name: Downey, Paul A.
title: Founder, Investment Banking Consultant
notes: Paul A. Downey is an investment banking consultant with over 50 years of experience. He began his career at First Boston in New York in 1966 after graduating from Yale College and serving in the U.S. Navy. He was a Partner at White Weld (1971-1978), then Managing Director at First Boston and Executive Director of Credit Suisse First Boston, before founding Downey Capital in 1991 to advise privately-owned U.S. companies. He resides in Healdsburg, California.
ngos: Board member: Pepperwood Preserve, Seven Hills Group; former boards: Santa Rosa Symphony, Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution, National Repertory Orchestra

name: Doyle, Richard Proctor Jr.
title: Partner, Attorney
notes: Richard Proctor Doyle Jr. is a partner at Doyle Low LLP in Lafayette, California, specializing in intellectual property litigation for technology-driven companies for over 35 years. He earned his B.S. in Chemistry from Creighton University and his J.D. from the University of San Francisco, and was an Adjunct Professor at USF Law School teaching Patent Litigation for over 10 years.

name: Elling, Kurt
title: Jazz Vocalist, Recording Artist
notes: Kurt Elling is a two-time Grammy Award-winning jazz vocalist, widely regarded as the standout male jazz voice of his generation. He has received 17 Grammy nominations and won Best Vocal Jazz Album for Dedicated to You (2009) and Secrets Are the Best Stories (2021). He studied at Gustavus Adolphus College and the University of Chicago Divinity School before signing with Blue Note Records in 1995.

name: Erickson, Nils
title: Owner, Audio Engineer
notes: Nils Erickson is a musician and owner of Erickson Sound Productions LLC, a professional sound company based in San Francisco, CA. He attended Berklee College of Music and provides audio services for weddings, concerts, corporate events, and political campaigns, having worked with Rock and Roll Hall-of-Famers and presidential nominees.

name: Evers, William Dohrmann Jr.
title: Managing Director
notes: William D. Evers Jr. ('Bill') is a Managing Director at AlTi Global in San Francisco, a fifth-generation San Franciscan with over 30 years in financial services. He previously served as Partner and Managing Director at Presidio Capital Advisors (2009+), as a Principal at Bernstein Global Wealth Management, and in institutional fixed-income roles at Alex. Brown & Sons and L.F. Rothschild. He holds a B.A. in Political Science from UC Berkeley.
ngos: Board member: California Academy of Sciences, Gladstone Institutes; former board chair, Keep Tahoe Blue (2015-2024); Greenbelt Alliance; Reading Partners; San Francisco Day School

name: Gasser, Nolan Ira
title: Chief Genomic Officer and Co-Founder
notes: Dr. Nolan Ira Gasser (born November 10, 1964) is a composer, pianist, musicologist, and music technologist best known as the architect of Pandora Radio's Music Genome Project, where he served as Chief Musicologist from 2000. He earned his Ph.D. in musicology from Stanford University and co-founded Katch Data, an AI content intelligence company. He is also a music consultant for Google/YouTube and author of WHY YOU LIKE IT (Macmillan, 2019).

name: Hansen, John C.

notes: John Cyril Hansen is founder and managing partner of JH Partners LLC, a San Francisco-based private equity firm focused on growth-oriented middle-market consumer products and services companies, founded in 1986. He has invested approximately $500 million in companies with revenues of $10 million to $300 million. He has served on boards of Design Within Reach, Frette, Jurlique, Bare Escentuals, and La Perla.

title: Founder, Golf Course Architect
notes: Robert Trent 'Bobby' Jones Jr. (born July 24, 1939) is an internationally renowned golf course architect who has designed more than 270 golf courses in over 40 countries on six continents. He attended Yale University (history and American Studies) and Stanford Law School before founding his own firm in Palo Alto, CA in the early 1970s. He has served as president of the American Society of Golf Course Architects and as chairman of the California State Park and Recreation Commission. He resides in Woodside, California.

name: Lovett, Marcus
title: Actor, Singer, Founder
notes: Marcus Lovett (born 1965 in Glen Ellyn, Illinois) is an American actor and singer who graduated from Carnegie Mellon University with honors. He has performed lead roles in The Phantom of the Opera, Les Miserables, Aspects of Love, Carousel, and King David on Broadway and in the West End. His voice is the trademark for Good Morning America, The David Letterman Show (17 years), and thousands of TV and radio commercials. He is founder of the nonprofit JoinedHands.

MacPhee Jr. (1933-2017), who was also a trustee of the foundation for 30+ years and worked as a CFO in real estate in San Anselmo, CA.

Parsons Jr. (1940-1995) was a folklorist and reference librarian at the Library of Congress American Folklife Center, known for coordinating the Folklife Reading Room and his work collecting waterfowl hunting traditions. The Gerald E. and Corinne L. Parsons Fund Award at the Library of Congress is named in his honor to increase awareness of ethnographic collections.

He began his career at International Paper Company in New York before purchasing controlling interest in Murphy Bonded Warehouse in 1976, becoming sole shareholder in 1986. The company operates over 750,000 square feet of warehouse space.
